==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marked
<hw>Marked</hw> <pr>(m⟦aum⟧rkt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Designated or
distinguished by, or as by, a mark; hence; noticeable; conspicuous;
<as>as, a <ex>marked</ex> card; a <ex>marked</ex> coin; a
<ex>marked</ex> instance.</as></def> -- <wordforms><wf>Mark"ed*ly</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <au>J. S. Mill.</au></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>A marked man</b></col>, <cd>a man who is noted by a
community, or by a part of it, as, for excellence or depravity; --
usually with an unfavorable suggestion.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Markee</ent>⟦br⟧
